1
00:00:13,400 --> 00:00:14,040
P’ Le!

2
00:00:15,560 --> 00:00:16,640
Don't cross the line.

3
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:19,840
You want it so badly?!
Then let's set a status.

4
00:00:21,120 --> 00:00:23,160
Hookup partners.
How about that?!

5
00:00:24,360 --> 00:00:27,000
If not, then get the hell out of my life!

6
00:00:36,720 --> 00:00:37,800
Rann, I’m sorry.

7
00:00:38,560 --> 00:00:40,000
Hi, darling!

8
00:00:41,240 --> 00:00:42,320
Can we just get to the point?

9
00:00:43,840 --> 00:00:46,000
You mean your plan to backstab your father?

10
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:11,720
Rann, can we please talk?

11
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:14,920
There is nothing to talk about.

12
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:17,560
There goes my boss’ pride.

13
00:01:29,240 --> 00:01:33,000
I think... you should make up with our boss.

14
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:35,720
She’s so pitiful.

15
00:01:36,120 --> 00:01:38,000
Just look at those eyes.

16
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:44,000
From a tiger… to a kitten.

17
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:47,720
She's basically meowing, I heard it.

18
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:51,880
I don't see anything pitiful about her.

19
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:53,960
Want me to look? Do it yourself.

20
00:01:55,759 --> 00:01:56,759
Aren't you two close?

21
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,080
Why are you taking it out on me?

22
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:06,360
I did my best, boss.

23
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:10,800
I told you not to put on airs so much.
Now look what happened.

24
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:12,960
What's the saying again?

25
00:02:14,040 --> 00:02:17,120
What goes around comes around, huh?

26
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:18,480
- Ai Peem.
- Yes, ma’am.

27
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:23,040
You brought this on yourself.
Don't look at me.

28
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:26,160
I think I’d better go.

29
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:29,520
Look who's whimpering like a dog.

30
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:32,400
Awooo!

31
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:15,760
Mad or not, I still have to give this to her.

32
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:19,600
Why am I acting like a child?

33
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:22,520
Keep it professional, Rann.

34
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:25,520
Remember what you're here for.

35
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:40,840
Khun Rann.

36
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:43,840
Can I help you with something?

37
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:46,720
Khun Kanin would like to see you.

38
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:53,880
Is there something you want to tell me?

39
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:00,560
No, sir.

40
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:04,160
Are you sure?

41
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:07,680
Yes.

42
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:19,920
Then what about you sneaking
into my office while I was out?

43
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:23,800
Me?

44
00:06:26,080 --> 00:06:27,920
When did I ever come in here?

45
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:29,600
Oh?

46
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:36,520
Do you mean when I came in
to look for the earrings?

47
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:40,600
But I did ask that day.

48
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,920
And Khun Pha was with me the whole time.

49
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:46,320
Is that the day you're talking about?

50
00:06:58,240 --> 00:07:03,920
I was indeed with her that day,
but not the entire time.

51
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:09,120
Because an intern spilled
coffee outside the office.

52
00:07:09,760 --> 00:07:11,320
When I came back,

53
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:17,960
I saw her getting up from
behind your desk before she left.

54
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:28,040
It's exactly as she said.

55
00:07:29,440 --> 00:07:30,280
I...

56
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:36,840
I only realized after
I walked out that I forgot them.

57
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,680
So I searched the whole building.

58
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:46,600
Your office was the only place left,
which is why I asked to come in.

59
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:54,760
Those earrings are a keepsake
from my grandmother.

60
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:58,240
They really mean the world to me.

61
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:01,520
I understand.

62
00:08:03,480 --> 00:08:06,480
After all, it's a keepsake
from someone important.

63
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:08,720
Yes.

64
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:12,120
Thank you for understanding, Khun Kanin.

65
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:14,320
So, may I leave now?

66
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:20,520
But as I recall...

67
00:08:22,760 --> 00:08:25,760
you never even came behind my desk.

68
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:28,800
So how could they end up here?

69
00:08:29,880 --> 00:08:30,720
Right?

70
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:45,480
Do you have something to tell me?

71
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:53,040
Khun Lené, you can't go in!
I have to inform the president first!

72
00:08:53,040 --> 00:08:54,000
Move!

73
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:59,320
Um... I tried to stop her,
but she wouldn't listen.

74
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:00,760
It's alright.

75
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:04,320
Why should anyone stop
a daughter from seeing her father?

76
00:09:05,560 --> 00:09:07,200
- You may leave.
- Yes, sir.

77
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,600
Is something the matter, sweetie?

78
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:18,080
What are you up to, Dad?

79
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:24,480
What am I up to?

80
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:27,400
Dad, Rann is my person.

81
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:31,640
Talk to me directly if you have a problem,
instead of summoning her like this.

82
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:35,920
Are you misunderstanding something?

83
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:40,920
I'm the one who hired Rann, not you.

84
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:41,960
So what?

85
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:44,120
She's still my person either way.

86
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:46,680
From the very start.

87
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:59,080
I’ve taught you since you were young—
never have a weakness.

88
00:10:01,880 --> 00:10:05,240
But Mom told me that no one is without weakness.

89
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:09,240
It’s a matter of whether we can protect it.

90
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:15,840
You mean... your dead mother?

91
00:10:21,520 --> 00:10:22,280
Let's go.

92
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:25,160
Wait.

93
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:31,800
Protect it well.

94
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:33,760
That weakness.

95
00:10:42,640 --> 00:10:44,600
Dig up everything on that girl's background.

96
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:48,760
And have someone check the computer
for anything suspicious.

97
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:50,960
Understood.

98
00:11:35,640 --> 00:11:36,560
P’ Le.

99
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:41,040
I'm fine.

100
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:44,400
He didn't do anything.

101
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:51,800
And I didn't report anything to him
beyond what we agreed on that day.

102
00:11:55,040 --> 00:11:56,200
Please believe me.

103
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:08,280
It's not that I don't believe you.

104
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:13,280
I'm just furious at what he did to you!

105
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:15,880
And what he said…

106
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:19,080
How dare he bring up Mom when—!

107
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:22,520
Dammit!

108
00:12:49,520 --> 00:12:50,800
I'm fine.

109
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:07,280
I know, Rann. I know.

110
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:10,720
But I’m just scared.

111
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,400
What are you scared of?

112
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:20,720
I’m scared of what he might do to you.

113
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:24,280
Scared of losing my Noo Rann again…

114
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:29,840
when we’re still fighting.

115
00:13:44,480 --> 00:13:46,000
It's okay, P' Le.

116
00:13:48,240 --> 00:13:49,600
I'm here now.

117
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:52,240
It’s okay.

118
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:02,000
I’m really fine.

119
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:04,320
Good thing you came just in time.

120
00:14:05,520 --> 00:14:09,200
This is exactly why I didn't
want to drag you into this.

121
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:11,320
I’m sorry.

122
00:14:13,880 --> 00:14:14,880
For which day?

123
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:19,560
Yesterday? Today?

124
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:21,880
Or the day I graduated?

125
00:14:28,640 --> 00:14:31,080
I figured you already knew.

126
00:14:32,760 --> 00:14:33,800
I don't.

127
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:39,120
Unless you tell me…
everything is just a guess.

128
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:59,000
You know, my mother had the most beautiful smile.

129
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:05,160
In my memory of her...
she was a kind person.

130
00:15:06,440 --> 00:15:07,920
Someone who loved volunteering.

131
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:13,200
And was brave enough
to help children in war zones.

132
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:21,400
Then a question came to mind:

133
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:27,320
Why did that kind woman have to be
shot dead by terrorists in a refugee camp?

134
00:15:30,520 --> 00:15:31,880
So I asked my father.

135
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:35,000
He said she was just unlucky.

136
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:37,760
But I didn’t believe him.

137
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:42,560
I don't know when I started
doubting every word he said.

138
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:49,040
I tried to find the truth and finally found it.

139
00:15:51,040 --> 00:15:56,360
Our supposedly clean family business
turned out to be unbelievably dirty.

140
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:59,960
My father smuggles everything, Rann.

141
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:02,680
From goods...

142
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:05,720
to people.

143
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:11,520
The moment my mother found out,
she did everything to stop him.

144
00:16:18,320 --> 00:16:19,680
But you see how that turned out.

145
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,960
And when I was feeling completely lost...

146
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:29,840
I was lucky to have met Peem.

147
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:35,200
My mother saved him when he was a child.

148
00:16:37,920 --> 00:16:41,280
He was the only one who tried
to find the truth about her death.

149
00:16:48,280 --> 00:16:49,440
I will never...

150
00:16:51,680 --> 00:16:54,480
forgive him for taking away
the person I love most.

151
00:16:57,720 --> 00:17:02,080
I'm going to bring him down
and make him pay for what he did.

152
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:25,599
I never wanted to push you away.

153
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:29,360
But I was so scared, Rann.

154
00:17:30,680 --> 00:17:32,760
What if something happened to you too?

155
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:34,640
What if he wanted to get rid of you too?

156
00:17:42,160 --> 00:17:44,360
Can you kiss me now, P’ Le?

157
00:18:24,120 --> 00:18:26,720
But I still haven't forgiven you for yesterday.

158
00:18:31,280 --> 00:18:34,320
I’m sorry. I was jealous.

159
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:39,080
I thought you were on your period.
You went totally ballistic.

160
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:43,360
So, can you forgive this hormonal mess?

161
00:18:44,640 --> 00:18:46,160
Give you an inch, and you take a mile.

162
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:48,480
I never miss an opportunity.

163
00:18:50,120 --> 00:18:51,440
Then promise me something first.

164
00:18:52,320 --> 00:18:53,200
What is it?

165
00:18:58,680 --> 00:18:59,600
P’ Le.

166
00:19:01,280 --> 00:19:02,040
Yes?

167
00:19:03,840 --> 00:19:07,960
Promise me that you'll never push me away again.

168
00:19:34,480 --> 00:19:35,560
I promise.

169
00:19:37,320 --> 00:19:38,880
I will protect you.

170
00:19:42,600 --> 00:19:43,600
Done talking now?

171
00:19:54,240 --> 00:19:56,240
Let's make a promise.

172
00:19:57,080 --> 00:19:59,680
P’ Le! We’re in the office!

173
00:20:00,480 --> 00:20:01,280
Exactly.

174
00:20:02,480 --> 00:20:04,080
It's the office, darling.

175
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,040
What are you doing here?!

176
00:20:14,160 --> 00:20:16,600
I thought you two were done making up.

177
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:19,840
But looks like you're moving on to phase two.

178
00:20:21,440 --> 00:20:23,040
Do you still want to keep your job?

179
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:26,320
Of course I do. That's why I'm here.

180
00:20:27,040 --> 00:20:28,560
Are we bringing Khun Rann along too?

181
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:36,360
There's something I want you to see.

182
00:20:37,680 --> 00:20:41,360
This time, let me be the one to tell you first.

183
00:20:50,960 --> 00:20:53,400
Welcome aboard, newbie.

184
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:18,800
What is all this?

185
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:22,800
This is my weapon.

186
00:21:25,440 --> 00:21:27,680
I don't work with that guy alone.

187
00:21:28,480 --> 00:21:30,840
Everyone here works for me.

188
00:21:31,840 --> 00:21:33,600
But this place looks abandoned from outside.

189
00:21:35,720 --> 00:21:38,360
How long have you been planning this?

190
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:41,600
Since the very second
I stepped into that company.

191
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:43,840
It's been six years now.

192
00:21:44,920 --> 00:21:50,640
It feels like a long time, but it's
nothing compared to his 30-year reign.

193
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:54,760
Khun Lené’s father has the nose of a bloodhound.

194
00:21:55,880 --> 00:22:00,400
Not sure if he's found this place yet,
but I doubt it.

195
00:22:02,640 --> 00:22:06,640
Our last base was completely destroyed.
We've had to relocate three times already.

196
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:09,840
Luckily, Khun Lené saw it coming last time.

197
00:22:11,920 --> 00:22:14,240
Come on. I’ll introduce you to everyone.

198
00:22:15,240 --> 00:22:16,240
Hold on, P’ Le.

199
00:22:17,280 --> 00:22:18,080
Hm?

200
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:20,840
I also have something to show you.

201
00:22:24,480 --> 00:22:26,560
TOP SECRET

202
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:30,400
I pulled some hidden data and found out
they're embezzling company funds.

203
00:22:30,520 --> 00:22:34,280
So I planned to use this
evidence to bring Khun Kanin down.

204
00:22:34,320 --> 00:22:36,280
But on closer inspection,

205
00:22:36,320 --> 00:22:40,880
almost all of this data is actually
leverage he uses against others.

206
00:22:41,120 --> 00:22:42,560
Check out this figure here.

207
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:50,120
Where did you get this data, Rann?

208
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:57,120
If I tell you, you won't
be mad at me, right?

209
00:23:02,120 --> 00:23:04,280
Out with it, you little rascal.

210
00:23:07,640 --> 00:23:08,680
I’m not a rascal.

211
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:16,000
Then tell me now... darling.

212
00:23:24,320 --> 00:23:28,960
Well... I sneaked into Khun Kanin's office.

213
00:23:30,560 --> 00:23:34,600
And... I used a little trick

214
00:23:35,080 --> 00:23:39,080
to copy the data from his computer.

215
00:23:39,240 --> 00:23:40,120
How?

216
00:23:40,600 --> 00:23:43,280
Do you remember Gen? My friend.

217
00:23:44,560 --> 00:23:45,920
She’s a hacker.

218
00:23:45,920 --> 00:23:48,320
- And she's really good at—
- Never do this again, Rann.

219
00:23:52,680 --> 00:23:54,440
- No promises.
- Rann.

220
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:56,640
Hm?

221
00:23:59,120 --> 00:24:00,520
But I'll tell you beforehand.

222
00:24:01,520 --> 00:24:03,080
Is that okay?

223
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:13,640
P’ Le.

224
00:24:14,920 --> 00:24:15,640
What?

225
00:24:18,480 --> 00:24:20,800
Thank you for telling me.

226
00:24:25,680 --> 00:24:27,760
Thank you for trusting me again.

227
00:24:31,120 --> 00:24:32,320
Thank you too.

228
00:24:35,320 --> 00:24:36,400
Thank you…

229
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:41,320
for going this far for me.

230
00:24:54,520 --> 00:24:58,400
I want to kiss you right now,
but we still have work to do.

231
00:25:03,080 --> 00:25:06,920
And I need to introduce you to someone.

232
00:25:32,840 --> 00:25:34,480
This is Dean, my close friend.

233
00:25:34,880 --> 00:25:37,040
He's the mole for this operation.

234
00:25:50,160 --> 00:25:52,840
We'll kick off our plan by acquiring
as many shares as possible.

235
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:02,920
How much has Dean acquired so far?

236
00:26:03,520 --> 00:26:04,880
14 percent.

237
00:26:05,040 --> 00:26:10,200
If we combine that with your shares,
we need 20 more to overtake Khun Kanin.

238
00:26:11,520 --> 00:26:14,680
You won’t regret choosing our side.

239
00:27:47,560 --> 00:27:48,800
Want some coffee, boss?

240
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:51,160
Mm, sure.

241
00:28:28,840 --> 00:28:30,880
Signature: Saran Hiranwathit

242
00:28:33,040 --> 00:28:36,400
I'm glad you made this decision, Uncle.

243
00:28:38,960 --> 00:28:40,960
It’s time for the younger
generation to take over.

244
00:28:41,320 --> 00:28:43,320
I’m dying to retire, anyway.

245
00:28:44,720 --> 00:28:48,120
But are you sure you can handle your father?

246
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:49,840
Yes.

247
00:28:50,560 --> 00:28:55,280
And I’ll make sure you won't get
into trouble or regret your choice.

248
00:28:55,840 --> 00:28:58,560
Thank you. I’ll take my leave now.

249
00:29:21,720 --> 00:29:22,640
P’ Le.

250
00:29:23,440 --> 00:29:24,200
Hm?

251
00:29:25,520 --> 00:29:29,600
Do you think this will be
enough to stop your father?

252
00:29:30,840 --> 00:29:33,080
Will it be enough to prevent your death?

253
00:29:33,800 --> 00:29:37,400
The one who’s going to
kill you is your father… right?

254
00:29:39,120 --> 00:29:40,120
I don't know for sure.

255
00:29:41,680 --> 00:29:45,440
But one thing is certain—
I want to take him down.

256
00:29:46,360 --> 00:29:51,040
At the very least, I need to strip him
of as much power as I can.

257
00:29:52,640 --> 00:29:56,160
I know that his reach extends
far beyond this company.

258
00:29:59,960 --> 00:30:07,160
And I’m well aware that
this fight won't end easily.

259
00:30:10,040 --> 00:30:11,800
Not until one of us…

260
00:30:14,160 --> 00:30:15,680
ends up dead.

261
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:23,560
Do you still want to help me?

262
00:30:32,800 --> 00:30:33,800
P’ Le.

263
00:30:39,720 --> 00:30:43,080
Can we make a quick stop before going home?

264
00:30:52,760 --> 00:30:54,160
This place hasn’t changed at all.

265
00:31:02,840 --> 00:31:04,200
Do you remember this place, P’ Le?

266
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:15,240
Get out of my sight.

267
00:31:28,600 --> 00:31:29,600
I’m sorry.

268
00:31:32,200 --> 00:31:33,360
What are you apologizing for?

269
00:31:35,680 --> 00:31:37,440
I’m sorry for what I said back then.

270
00:31:39,040 --> 00:31:40,480
I’m sorry for driving you away.

271
00:31:43,040 --> 00:31:45,320
But I never wanted to hurt you.

272
00:31:46,920 --> 00:31:49,040
Believe me, Rann. I’m sorry—

273
00:31:53,960 --> 00:31:55,920
You’ve apologized enough.

274
00:31:58,720 --> 00:32:00,440
I want to apologize to you too.

275
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:04,400
I’m sorry for running away
without asking you anything

276
00:32:05,600 --> 00:32:06,920
and just jumped to conclusions.

277
00:32:11,960 --> 00:32:13,160
But look at this, P’ Le.

278
00:32:16,440 --> 00:32:18,840
We’re back standing right here again.

279
00:32:20,480 --> 00:32:21,520
Just like before.

280
00:32:22,760 --> 00:32:23,760
That’s enough, isn’t it?

281
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:31,880
It’s been so long since I’ve been here.
Maybe we should go see the professors?

282
00:32:34,480 --> 00:32:35,200
Rann.

283
00:32:39,960 --> 00:32:40,720
Yes?

284
00:32:41,840 --> 00:32:42,840
Thank you…

285
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:46,000
for coming back.

286
00:32:58,840 --> 00:33:01,160
Thank you for being by my side again.

287
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:17,200
I’m back.

288
00:33:21,600 --> 00:33:23,240
I’m back, P’ Le.

289
00:33:32,200 --> 00:33:35,520
~ Since the moment of my return ~

290
00:33:35,560 --> 00:33:38,840
~ I realized I came back for you ~

291
00:33:38,880 --> 00:33:41,520
~ I’ve come back to make things right ~

292
00:33:41,520 --> 00:33:45,320
~ For the day I left you all alone ~

293
00:33:45,320 --> 00:33:48,640
~ From now on, I’ll never let you...

294
00:33:48,640 --> 00:33:52,320
P’ Le... no matter how many choices I have,

295
00:33:53,960 --> 00:33:55,400
I’ll always choose this path.

296
00:33:56,360 --> 00:33:59,320
I will do whatever it takes
to be by your side again.

297
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:01,720
Just as long as you’re here.

298
00:39:36,480 --> 00:39:37,440
Is something the matter?

299
00:39:38,080 --> 00:39:41,360
I’m surprised you wanted
to see me out of the blue.

300
00:39:45,040 --> 00:39:49,840
A little. Actually...
I just ran into your daughter.

301
00:40:11,720 --> 00:40:13,040
I’m so happy.

302
00:40:14,240 --> 00:40:15,400
Me too.

303
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:18,920
Not as much as I am.

304
00:40:20,280 --> 00:40:21,720
What do you mean 'not as much'?

305
00:40:22,200 --> 00:40:24,200
You have no idea what I’ve been through.

306
00:40:25,120 --> 00:40:27,480
You don't know what I’ve been through either.

307
00:40:35,480 --> 00:40:38,920
You once said that I’m your entire world.

308
00:40:39,800 --> 00:40:41,960
You’re my entire world too.

309
00:40:53,680 --> 00:40:59,160
The day you left... was the day
my whole world fell apart too.

310
00:41:01,760 --> 00:41:02,640
P’ Le…

311
00:41:06,760 --> 00:41:08,440
There’s something I want to tell you.

312
00:41:09,640 --> 00:41:11,520
I have something to tell you too.

313
00:41:12,240 --> 00:41:13,080
What is it?

314
00:41:14,080 --> 00:41:16,800
You go first. Don’t cheat.

315
00:41:25,880 --> 00:41:27,160
I’ll let you go first.

316
00:41:28,600 --> 00:41:29,440
Fine.

317
00:41:34,280 --> 00:41:34,880
Hm?

318
00:41:42,440 --> 00:41:44,000
P’ Le loves Noo Rann.

319
00:41:49,840 --> 00:41:50,840
Did you hear me?

320
00:41:53,440 --> 00:41:54,920
Looks like you didn’t.

321
00:41:56,560 --> 00:41:58,080
P’ Le loves Noo Rann.

322
00:41:58,240 --> 00:42:00,560
Love you. So much. More than anything.

323
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:02,000
Do you hear me now?

324
00:42:02,640 --> 00:42:03,960
Are you teasing me?

325
00:42:09,760 --> 00:42:10,760
I love you.

326
00:42:14,880 --> 00:42:16,040
Me too.

327
00:42:19,920 --> 00:42:23,600
What 'me too'?
I won't know unless you tell me.

328
00:42:42,280 --> 00:42:43,800
Noo Rann loves P’ Le too.

329
00:42:48,920 --> 00:42:50,160
I always have.

330
00:42:54,840 --> 00:42:56,320
All this time.

331
00:43:01,720 --> 00:43:03,120
‘Noo’ is not my name.

332
00:43:03,880 --> 00:43:04,480
Oh?

333
00:43:05,120 --> 00:43:08,960
You keep referring to yourself as ‘Noo,’
so I thought that was your name.

334
00:43:09,400 --> 00:43:10,400
That’s not it at all.

335
00:43:13,720 --> 00:43:17,920
Whether it’s in this life or the last...
I’ve always loved you.

336
00:43:24,840 --> 00:43:25,720
Rann.

337
00:43:26,480 --> 00:43:27,240
Hm?

338
00:43:28,560 --> 00:43:30,560
If you don’t like this house,

339
00:43:32,200 --> 00:43:34,080
should we look for a new one together?

340
00:43:35,360 --> 00:43:39,600
And if you don't like this car,
let’s pick out a new one.

341
00:43:40,360 --> 00:43:43,280
One that I’ll use to take you everywhere.

342
00:43:44,360 --> 00:43:45,240
Sounds good?

343
00:43:46,520 --> 00:43:52,080
I once told my grandma that
after I graduate and get a job,

344
00:43:53,640 --> 00:43:57,240
I'll buy a big car so I can drive her everywhere.

345
00:43:57,760 --> 00:44:01,960
Then once you can buy it,
I’ll let you drive me around instead.

346
00:44:07,080 --> 00:44:08,280
You remember.

347
00:44:09,640 --> 00:44:11,480
I remember everything about you.

348
00:44:13,280 --> 00:44:15,600
I want you to be my family.

349
00:44:17,320 --> 00:44:18,480
Come live with me.

350
00:44:24,720 --> 00:44:26,640
Hey now, don't cry.

351
00:44:28,200 --> 00:44:30,200
Don't cry when you're with me, okay?

352
00:44:31,360 --> 00:44:33,720
You have to be very happy.

353
00:44:37,240 --> 00:44:39,160
‘I hope you’re always happy,’ remember?

354
00:44:42,360 --> 00:44:43,800
P’ Le…

355
00:45:53,240 --> 00:45:55,080
I already have my own necklace.

356
00:45:55,680 --> 00:46:00,120
It's worth thousands of times
more than what you're giving me.

357
00:46:12,360 --> 00:46:13,360
Red thread?

358
00:46:39,600 --> 00:46:41,320
Where’s your wife… oops!

359
00:46:42,800 --> 00:46:44,000
I mean, your secretary?

360
00:46:46,480 --> 00:46:47,920
She's. Resting.

361
00:46:51,040 --> 00:46:54,600
How is she resting?
She seemed perfectly fine yesterday.

362
00:46:57,920 --> 00:47:00,320
Why? You want the details?

363
00:47:01,520 --> 00:47:04,320
Judging by your look,
asking more is a death wish.

364
00:47:04,320 --> 00:47:05,440
I’d rather not know.

365
00:47:06,560 --> 00:47:09,400
You've improved.
You can actually read the room.

366
00:47:10,840 --> 00:47:13,080
Ever since you got a 'wife,' boss,

367
00:47:14,400 --> 00:47:16,120
your sense of humor has upgraded.

368
00:47:30,600 --> 00:47:31,360
Khun Lené.

369
00:47:32,080 --> 00:47:32,720
Hm?

370
00:47:33,800 --> 00:47:36,000
I know you moved the plan forward

371
00:47:37,200 --> 00:47:38,880
to get this over with as soon as possible.

372
00:47:40,880 --> 00:47:42,240
But aren’t you moving too fast?

373
00:47:44,320 --> 00:47:46,160
I’m worried your father might catch on.

374
00:47:47,800 --> 00:47:49,240
I know you're worried.

375
00:47:51,480 --> 00:47:53,720
But I want everything
taken care of as soon as possible.

376
00:47:56,200 --> 00:48:00,280
At least, I need to make sure that
Rann is safe while she's with me.

377
00:48:02,520 --> 00:48:04,280
I don't ever want to send her away again.

378
00:48:05,720 --> 00:48:06,640
Besides…

379
00:48:13,880 --> 00:48:14,760
Just say it.

380
00:48:16,400 --> 00:48:18,200
You know you can talk to me about anything.

381
00:48:22,920 --> 00:48:23,840
I'm scared.

382
00:48:27,360 --> 00:48:29,120
I'm scared something might happen to Rann...

383
00:48:31,800 --> 00:48:32,760
just like Mom.

384
00:48:39,520 --> 00:48:41,040
Alright. Let's do this.

385
00:48:42,520 --> 00:48:44,840
Since you've put it that way, boss,

386
00:48:44,840 --> 00:48:46,680
what choice does
a mere servant like me have?

387
00:48:48,080 --> 00:48:49,680
We'll take it one problem at a time.

388
00:48:51,200 --> 00:48:53,200
Starting with taking down your father.

389
00:48:58,240 --> 00:48:59,000
Peem.

390
00:49:01,080 --> 00:49:01,880
Yes?

391
00:49:03,920 --> 00:49:05,480
You're not a servant.

392
00:49:10,080 --> 00:49:11,680
You're like a big brother to me.

393
00:49:23,240 --> 00:49:24,640
Then you should know

394
00:49:25,560 --> 00:49:28,920
that this brother is more than
willing to help his little sister.

395
00:49:35,240 --> 00:49:36,200
Cut it out.

396
00:49:37,640 --> 00:49:40,360
How's the matter I asked
you to handle coming along?

397
00:49:45,440 --> 00:49:46,720
So much for the touching moment.

398
00:49:47,640 --> 00:49:48,800
Back to work it is.

399
00:49:55,720 --> 00:49:56,640
I'm off then.

400
00:50:34,320 --> 00:50:35,320
This isn’t real.

401
00:50:45,880 --> 00:50:46,720
It can’t be.

402
00:50:48,640 --> 00:50:49,840
It's not time yet.

403
00:50:50,520 --> 00:50:51,880
There are still months left.

404
00:50:52,360 --> 00:50:53,760
Why is this happening?!

405
00:51:04,400 --> 00:51:06,280
It's not time yet.

406
00:51:06,320 --> 00:51:08,040
Why did it turn out like this?!

407
00:51:10,640 --> 00:51:11,480
P’ Le!

408
00:51:12,480 --> 00:51:13,360
P’ Le.

409
00:51:51,840 --> 00:51:54,240
P’ Dia, where did P’ Le go?

410
00:51:54,800 --> 00:51:56,560
She left for the office early this morning.

411
00:51:57,040 --> 00:52:00,880
Khun Lené told me not to wake you up.
She wanted you to get some rest.

412
00:52:01,440 --> 00:52:02,880
And, this is for you.

413
00:52:10,920 --> 00:52:14,160
For the one
who makes my world brighter.

414
00:52:21,440 --> 00:52:24,520
I have to go to the office.
There's something I need to tell P’ Le.

415
00:52:24,760 --> 00:52:27,480
Alright, I'll go get the driver right away.

416
00:52:27,960 --> 00:52:29,240
Okay, thank you.

417
00:53:09,080 --> 00:53:10,520
I have to tell P’ Le everything.

418
00:53:11,240 --> 00:53:13,120
What's going to happen to her,

419
00:53:13,680 --> 00:53:15,400
and the fact that I turned back in time.

420
00:53:21,920 --> 00:53:24,960
Keep quiet... if you want to stay alive.

421
00:53:26,600 --> 00:53:27,400
You…

422
00:53:34,600 --> 00:53:35,960
The boss wants to see you.

423
00:53:38,520 --> 00:53:39,640
Move! Hurry!

424
00:53:52,960 --> 00:53:55,080
What's up?
Did you already give her the flowers?

425
00:53:56,680 --> 00:53:59,040
Khun Lené! Khun Rann has disappeared!

426
00:53:59,880 --> 00:54:02,720
When I came out of the house,
she was already gone!

427
00:54:03,160 --> 00:54:04,240
What happened?!

428
00:54:38,440 --> 00:54:39,360
Perfect.

429
00:54:41,440 --> 00:54:44,160
P' Le! You scared me.

430
00:54:44,680 --> 00:54:46,360
What are you making, hmm?

431
00:54:49,200 --> 00:54:50,400
Clear soup.

432
00:54:52,120 --> 00:54:54,000
What made you want to cook anyway?

433
00:54:54,400 --> 00:54:57,920
Work is already tiring enough.
You could have just let someone else do this.

434
00:54:59,000 --> 00:55:01,880
Yes, work is already tiring enough.

435
00:55:03,720 --> 00:55:04,640
I told you.

436
00:55:07,000 --> 00:55:10,080
I'm talking about you.
You're the one who's working so hard.

437
00:55:11,040 --> 00:55:13,080
That's why I'm cooking for you.

438
00:55:20,880 --> 00:55:23,920
Since you once told me
that you'd drive me anywhere,

439
00:55:24,760 --> 00:55:30,640
I secretly thought to myself that
if I got to be with you, I'd cook for you.

440
00:55:33,560 --> 00:55:35,400
I'll cook all your favorite dishes.

441
00:55:36,840 --> 00:55:39,320
Now that we’re living under the same roof,

442
00:55:39,840 --> 00:55:42,480
- it just feels...
- ...like we’re a married couple.

443
00:55:43,880 --> 00:55:44,880
It’s so nice.

444
00:55:50,320 --> 00:55:53,320
And besides food...

445
00:56:01,120 --> 00:56:02,440
can I eat something else too?

446
00:56:04,320 --> 00:56:05,320
Pervert!

447
00:56:08,200 --> 00:56:10,400
Can't you just stay romantic
instead of teasing me?

448
00:56:20,680 --> 00:56:23,040
But it's not like I've ever said no.

449
00:56:30,800 --> 00:56:32,200
Well...

450
00:56:35,440 --> 00:56:36,880
go ahead and eat.

451
00:56:40,280 --> 00:56:41,160
Come here!

452
00:56:43,960 --> 00:56:45,760
Aren’t you getting bold, hmm?

453
00:56:46,600 --> 00:56:47,360
Not at all.

454
00:56:47,400 --> 00:56:49,840
English Subtitles by Saowalak K.
P' Le!

455
00:56:50,760 --> 00:56:52,880
- Khun Lené!
- What is it? Did you find her?

456
00:56:53,160 --> 00:56:55,720
Your father contacted me,
saying he’s got work for me to do.

457
00:56:56,160 --> 00:56:59,400
You know what it means... don't you?

458
00:57:00,520 --> 00:57:04,160
We just met not long ago, Noo Rann.
But you look an absolute mess.

459
00:57:13,880 --> 00:57:14,480
No!

460
00:57:14,520 --> 00:57:16,240
I figured it would turn out like this.

461
00:57:16,280 --> 00:57:18,760
But I never imagined it would end this way.
